{"sections":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Cambium is a Swift-native concrete syntax tree library. This","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"tutorial series walks you through building a small but","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"production-shaped calculator language end-to-end: a recursive-","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"descent parser that produces a lossless tree, a typed AST overlay,","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"an evaluator with memoized analysis, persistent edits with","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"identity-preserving witnesses, an incremental reparse loop, fork-","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"join evaluation across structured-concurrent tasks, parallel","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"parsing with externalized interning, and on-disk serialization.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Each chapter culminates in REPL commands you can try in the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"companion sample at ","type":"text"},{"code":"Examples\/Calculator","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":". By the end you will","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"have built the same library that backs the ","type":"text"},{"code":"calc-repl","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"executable, one Cambium subsystem at a time.","type":"text"}]}],"action":{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"overridingTitleInlineContent":[{"text":"Get started","type":"text"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.cambium.Cambium\/tutorials\/Cambium\/01-DefineLanguage","overridingTitle":"Get started"},"kind":"hero","title":"Build a Calculator with Cambium"},{"image":null,"content":[],"name":null,"kind":"volume","chapters":[{"image":"chapter-banner.png","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Cambium represents a parsed document as a homogeneous green tree","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"whose nodes are tagged with a kind. In this chapter you define the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"calculator’s grammar, drive a builder from a recursive-descent","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"parser, and add Pratt-style precedence and parser-level error","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"recovery so the resulting tree round-trips even malformed input.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"tutorials":["doc:\/\/org.cambium.Cambium\/tutorials\/Cambium\/01-DefineLanguage","doc:\/\/org.cambium.Cambium\/tutorials\/Cambium\/02-DriveBuilder","doc:\/\/org.cambium.Cambium\/tutorials\/Cambium\/03-PrecedenceAndRecovery"],"name":"Build a Lossless CST"},{"image":"chapter-banner.png","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Once a tree exists, consumers need to walk it, query it by byte","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"position, and project a typed view for kind-specific work. This","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"chapter introduces borrowed cursors, owned handles, byte-streaming","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"text reads, and a typed AST overlay generated from the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.cambium.Cambium\/documentation\/CambiumSyntaxMacros\/CambiumSyntaxNode(_:for:)","isActive":true},{"text":" macro, then uses","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"them to build a recursive evaluator.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"tutorials":["doc:\/\/org.cambium.Cambium\/tutorials\/Cambium\/04-ReadingTree","doc:\/\/org.cambium.Cambium\/tutorials\/Cambium\/05-TypedAST","doc:\/\/org.cambium.Cambium\/tutorials\/Cambium\/06-Evaluator"],"name":"Read and Model the Tree"},{"image":"chapter-banner.png","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Cambium’s trees are persistent: editing produces a new tree","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"sharing as much green storage as possible, with a witness","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"describing the structural change. This chapter wires up constant","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"folding via subtree replacement, an incremental reparse loop with","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"a reuse oracle, and memoized analysis caches whose entries","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"survive edits by translating through the witnesses.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"tutorials":["doc:\/\/org.cambium.Cambium\/tutorials\/Cambium\/07-ReplacementWitnesses","doc:\/\/org.cambium.Cambium\/tutorials\/Cambium\/08-IncrementalReparse","doc:\/\/org.cambium.Cambium\/tutorials\/Cambium\/09-AnalysisTranslation"],"name":"Edit, Reparse, and Memoize"},{"image":"chapter-banner.png","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Cambium’s trees promote into ","type":"text"},{"code":"CambiumCore\/SharedSyntaxTree","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"snapshots that are ","type":"text"},{"code":"Sendable","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" and safe to share across tasks. In","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"this chapter you write a structured-concurrent fork-join","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"evaluator, parse a workload of expressions in parallel through a","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"shared token interner, and serialize a tree to disk for","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"editor-style warm restarts.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"tutorials":["doc:\/\/org.cambium.Cambium\/tutorials\/Cambium\/10-ForkJoinEval","doc:\/\/org.cambium.Cambium\/tutorials\/Cambium\/11-ParallelParse","doc:\/\/org.cambium.Cambium\/tutorials\/Cambium\/12-Serialization"],"name":"Concurrency and Persistence"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Reference material that complements the hands-on tutorials.","type":"text"}]}],"kind":"resources","tiles":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Articles in the Cambium documentation that complement the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"hands-on path:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"“Getting Started” — narrative skim of the API.","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"“Calculator” — sample-code overview.","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"“Externalized Interning” — deep dive on ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"TokenInterner"},{"text":".","type":"text"}]}]}],"type":"unorderedList"}],"identifier":"documentation","title":"Documentation","action":{"destination":"https:\/\/xn--wxa.dog\/cambium\/documentation\/cambium\/","title":"View more","type":"link"}},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The calculator example is a standalone SwiftPM package at","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"Examples\/Calculator","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":". Each tutorial cites the file in that","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"example whose canonical implementation it builds toward —","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"read them side by side once you have finished the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"corresponding tutorial.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"identifier":"https:\/\/github.com\/daig\/cambium\/tree\/main\/Examples\/Calculator","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":" — the full sample.","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"identifier":"https:\/\/github.com\/daig\/cambium\/blob\/main\/Examples\/Calculator\/README.md","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":" — REPL command reference.","type":"text"}]}]}],"type":"unorderedList"}],"identifier":"sampleCode","title":"Sample Code","action":{"destination":"https:\/\/github.com\/daig\/cambium\/tree\/main\/Examples\/Calculator","title":"View more","type":"link"}}]}],"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/tutorials\/tableofcontents"]}],"metadata":{"category":"Cambium","estimatedTime":"4hr 50min","role":"overview","categoryPathComponent":"TableOfContents","title":"Build a Calculator with Cambium"},"kind":"overview","identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/org.cambium.Cambium\/tutorials\/TableOfContents"},"hierarchy":{"reference":"doc:\/\/org.cambium.Cambium\/tutorials\/TableOfContents","paths":[]},"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"patch":0,"major":0},"references":{"doc://org.cambium.Cambium/tutorials/Cambium/03-PrecedenceAndRecovery":{"kind":"project","type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.cambium.Cambium\/tutorials\/Cambium\/03-PrecedenceAndRecovery","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The parser from the previous tutorial handles only “atomic”"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"prefix forms — literals and parenthesized groups. To parse"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"1 + 2 * 3"},{"type":"text","text":" correctly the parser needs operator precedence; to"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"survive "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"1 +"},{"type":"text","text":" or "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"(2"},{"type":"text","text":" it needs error recovery."}],"estimatedTime":"30min","url":"\/tutorials\/cambium\/03-precedenceandrecovery","title":"Add Precedence and Error Recovery","role":"project"},"doc://org.cambium.Cambium/tutorials/Cambium/12-Serialization":{"kind":"project","type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.cambium.Cambium\/tutorials\/Cambium\/12-Serialization","abstract":[{"text":"Cambium can serialize a tree to a compact byte stream and","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"decode it back. The format is length-, hash-, and","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"kind-validated at every record, so flipped bytes produce","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"named errors at decode time rather than silently malformed","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"trees.","type":"text"}],"estimatedTime":"15min","url":"\/tutorials\/cambium\/12-serialization","title":"Save and Load Trees","role":"project"},"doc://org.cambium.Cambium/documentation/CambiumSyntaxMacros/CambiumSyntaxNode(_:for:)":{"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Generate the standard stored syntax handle and unchecked initializer for a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"concrete typed syntax-node wrapper."}],"type":"topic","title":"CambiumSyntaxNode(_:for:)","url":"\/documentation\/cambiumsyntaxmacros\/cambiumsyntaxnode(_:for:)","kind":"symbol","role":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.cambium.Cambium\/documentation\/CambiumSyntaxMacros\/CambiumSyntaxNode(_:for:)","fragments":[{"text":"macro","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"CambiumSyntaxNode","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"<","kind":"text"},{"text":"Kind","kind":"genericParameter"},{"text":">(","kind":"text"},{"text":"Kind","preciseIdentifier":"s:19CambiumSyntaxMacros4KindL_xmfp","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":".Type, ","kind":"text"},{"text":"for","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"text":"Kind","preciseIdentifier":"s:19CambiumSyntaxMacros4KindL_xmfp","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":")","kind":"text"}]},"doc://org.cambium.Cambium/tutorials/Cambium/04-ReadingTree":{"kind":"project","type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.cambium.Cambium\/tutorials\/Cambium\/04-ReadingTree","abstract":[{"text":"A Cambium tree is meant to be queried frequently — by IDEs on","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"every keystroke, by analyzers walking every node, by formatters","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"emitting bytes. To stay within reasonable memory and ARC","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"budgets the primary traversal API is borrowed: walks happen","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"through ","type":"text"},{"code":"~Copyable","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" cursors handed to a closure, and source","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"text is exposed as a chunk-streaming view rather than a","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"materialized ","type":"text"},{"code":"String","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"estimatedTime":"25min","url":"\/tutorials\/cambium\/04-readingtree","title":"Read the Tree Without Allocating","role":"project"},"https://github.com/daig/cambium/tree/main/Examples/Calculator":{"title":"Examples\/Calculator","identifier":"https:\/\/github.com\/daig\/cambium\/tree\/main\/Examples\/Calculator","titleInlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Examples\/Calculator"}],"url":"https:\/\/github.com\/daig\/cambium\/tree\/main\/Examples\/Calculator","type":"link"},"doc://org.cambium.Cambium/tutorials/Cambium/08-IncrementalReparse":{"kind":"project","type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.cambium.Cambium\/tutorials\/Cambium\/08-IncrementalReparse","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"An IDE re-runs the parser on every keystroke. Reparsing the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"whole document each time is wasteful when most subtrees did"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"not change. "},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.cambium.Cambium\/documentation\/CambiumIncremental","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" exposes the four pieces"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"you wire together for "},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"subtree-level","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":" reuse:"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CambiumIncremental\/IncrementalParseSession"},{"type":"text","text":" (long-lived"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"bookkeeping), "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CambiumIncremental\/ReuseOracle"},{"type":"text","text":" (the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"parser-facing query API), "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CambiumIncremental\/TextEdit"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"(the change description), and"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CambiumIncremental\/ParseWitness"},{"type":"text","text":" (the post-parse summary"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"of what was reused)."}],"estimatedTime":"30min","url":"\/tutorials\/cambium\/08-incrementalreparse","title":"Incrementally Reparse","role":"project"},"doc://org.cambium.Cambium/tutorials/Cambium/02-DriveBuilder":{"kind":"project","type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.cambium.Cambium\/tutorials\/Cambium\/02-DriveBuilder","abstract":[{"text":"With the kind enum in place, you can write a recursive-descent","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"parser that emits into a ","type":"text"},{"code":"CambiumBuilder\/GreenTreeBuilder","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":". The","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"builder accepts a stream of ","type":"text"},{"code":"startNode","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" \/ ","type":"text"},{"code":"token","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" \/ ","type":"text"},{"code":"staticToken","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"\/ ","type":"text"},{"code":"finishNode","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" calls and produces a green tree whose structure","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"mirrors the calls one-for-one.","type":"text"}],"estimatedTime":"25min","url":"\/tutorials\/cambium\/02-drivebuilder","title":"Drive a GreenTreeBuilder","role":"project"},"doc://org.cambium.Cambium/tutorials/Cambium/05-TypedAST":{"kind":"project","type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.cambium.Cambium\/tutorials\/Cambium\/05-TypedAST","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Cambium’s CST stores everything as homogeneous nodes tagged"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"with a kind. That uniformity is what makes editing and reuse"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"cheap, but it leaves consumers to write "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"switch node.kind { ... }"},{"type":"text","text":" everywhere they want kind-specific behavior."}],"estimatedTime":"25min","url":"\/tutorials\/cambium\/05-typedast","title":"Project a Typed AST Overlay","role":"project"},"doc://org.cambium.Cambium/documentation/CambiumIncremental":{"abstract":[],"type":"topic","title":"CambiumIncremental","url":"\/documentation\/cambiumincremental","kind":"symbol","role":"collection","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.cambium.Cambium\/documentation\/CambiumIncremental"},"doc://org.cambium.Cambium/tutorials/Cambium/09-AnalysisTranslation":{"kind":"project","type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.cambium.Cambium\/tutorials\/Cambium\/09-AnalysisTranslation","abstract":[{"text":"The witnesses you built in Tutorial 7 (replacement) and","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Tutorial 8 (reparse) exist to make analysis caches ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"survive","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"edits","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"text":". Without translation every keystroke would invalidate","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"every memoized value — defeating the whole point of an","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"incremental tool.","type":"text"}],"estimatedTime":"30min","url":"\/tutorials\/cambium\/09-analysistranslation","title":"Translate Analysis Across Edits","role":"project"},"doc://org.cambium.Cambium/tutorials/TableOfContents":{"kind":"overview","type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.cambium.Cambium\/tutorials\/TableOfContents","abstract":[{"text":"Cambium is a Swift-native concrete syntax tree library. This","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"tutorial series walks you through building a small but","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"production-shaped calculator language end-to-end: a recursive-","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"descent parser that produces a lossless tree, a typed AST overlay,","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"an evaluator with memoized analysis, persistent edits with","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"identity-preserving witnesses, an incremental reparse loop, fork-","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"join evaluation across structured-concurrent tasks, parallel","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"parsing with externalized interning, and on-disk serialization.","type":"text"}],"url":"\/tutorials\/tableofcontents","title":"Build a Calculator with Cambium","role":"overview"},"https://github.com/daig/cambium/blob/main/Examples/Calculator/README.md":{"titleInlineContent":[{"code":"README.md","type":"codeVoice"}],"url":"https:\/\/github.com\/daig\/cambium\/blob\/main\/Examples\/Calculator\/README.md","type":"link","identifier":"https:\/\/github.com\/daig\/cambium\/blob\/main\/Examples\/Calculator\/README.md","title":"README.md"},"doc://org.cambium.Cambium/tutorials/Cambium/07-ReplacementWitnesses":{"kind":"project","type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.cambium.Cambium\/tutorials\/Cambium\/07-ReplacementWitnesses","abstract":[{"text":"Cambium trees are persistent: there is no in-place mutation.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"SharedSyntaxTree.replacing(_:with:context:)","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" produces a ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"new","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"tree that shares as much green storage with","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"the old as possible, and returns a","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"CambiumCore\/ReplacementWitness","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" describing the structural","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"change.","type":"text"}],"estimatedTime":"25min","url":"\/tutorials\/cambium\/07-replacementwitnesses","title":"Replace Subtrees with Witnesses","role":"project"},"doc://org.cambium.Cambium/tutorials/Cambium/01-DefineLanguage":{"type":"topic","url":"\/tutorials\/cambium\/01-definelanguage","kind":"project","role":"project","estimatedTime":"15min","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.cambium.Cambium\/tutorials\/Cambium\/01-DefineLanguage","title":"Define the Calculator Language","abstract":[{"text":"Every Cambium grammar starts with a kind enumeration: one case per","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"token and one per node the parser can produce. The kind enum","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"becomes the ","type":"text"},{"code":"Kind","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" associated type of a ","type":"text"},{"code":"CambiumCore\/SyntaxLanguage","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"conformance, and Cambium specializes its generic types around that","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"language to make tree storage compact and traversal type-safe.","type":"text"}]},"doc://org.cambium.Cambium/tutorials/Cambium/11-ParallelParse":{"type":"topic","url":"\/tutorials\/cambium\/11-parallelparse","kind":"project","role":"project","estimatedTime":"25min","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.cambium.Cambium\/tutorials\/Cambium\/11-ParallelParse","title":"Parallel Parsing with Shared Interning","abstract":[{"text":"Parallel parsing splits work across worker tasks: each","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"worker parses an independent subtree concurrently, then a","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"master builder splices the worker results into one logical","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"tree. The correctness-critical question is how the workers","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"share token-text vocabulary and the green-node namespace.","type":"text"}]},"doc://org.cambium.Cambium/tutorials/Cambium/10-ForkJoinEval":{"kind":"project","type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.cambium.Cambium\/tutorials\/Cambium\/10-ForkJoinEval","abstract":[{"code":"CambiumCore\/SharedSyntaxTree","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" is ","type":"text"},{"code":"Sendable","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":". Cambium’s red","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"layer realizes lazily under lock-free atomic slots, so two","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"tasks descending into different siblings of the same parent","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"never observe inconsistent state. The typed AST overlays are","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"also ","type":"text"},{"code":"Sendable, Hashable","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", so passing a sub-expression to a","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"child task is just an argument pass.","type":"text"}],"estimatedTime":"25min","url":"\/tutorials\/cambium\/10-forkjoineval","title":"Fork-Join Evaluation Across Tasks","role":"project"},"chapter-banner.png":{"variants":[{"url":"\/images\/org.cambium.Cambium\/chapter-banner.png","traits":["1x","light"]}],"type":"image","identifier":"chapter-banner.png","alt":"Chapter banner"},"doc://org.cambium.Cambium/tutorials/Cambium/06-Evaluator":{"type":"topic","url":"\/tutorials\/cambium\/06-evaluator","kind":"project","role":"project","estimatedTime":"20min","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.cambium.Cambium\/tutorials\/Cambium\/06-Evaluator","title":"Evaluate the Typed AST","abstract":[{"text":"With the typed AST in place from Tutorial 5, an evaluator","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"becomes a recursive function that pattern-matches on","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"ExprSyntax","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":". Each kind has a closed structure — its operands","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"and operator are addressable through the typed accessors —","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"so the evaluator stays small and total.","type":"text"}]}}}